\subsection{Taxonomic cleaning}{

Raw taxonomic entries contained numerous typographic errors introduced
during data entry. Cleaning was performed in three stages:

\enumerate{
\item \strong{Genus-level typos} — exact-match corrections for misspelled
genera (e.g. \code{"Ocrinus"} → \code{"Orcinus"},
\code{"Loxodona"} → \code{"Loxodonta"}).
\item \strong{Species-level typos} — corrections matched on both genus and
species to avoid cross-genus collisions (e.g.
\code{Balaenoptera "musuclus"} → \code{"musculus"}).
\item \strong{Formatting artefacts} — author suffixes (trailing \code{"L."}),
stray backticks, species epithets smuggled into the genus field, and
parenthetical synonyms were standardised.
}
}

\subsection{Excluded rows}{

The following categories of rows were excluded from this dataset pending
manual review. They can be re-added to \code{data-raw/taxa.R} once resolved:

\itemize{
\item \strong{Nomenclatural reclassifications} — taxa where the genus used
by authors differs from the currently accepted name (e.g. \emph{Anas}
spp. since split into \emph{Mareca}, \emph{Spatula}, and
\emph{Sibirionetta}; \emph{Puffinus} shearwaters moved to
\emph{Ardenna}; \emph{Grus} cranes moved to \emph{Antigone};
\emph{Phoca} seals moved to \emph{Pusa}).
\item \strong{Domestic/feral/subspecies ambiguity} — entries where multiple
names are in common use for the same animal (\emph{Canis lupus
